"Personnel is required to keep quiet from 6 PM to 6 AM.\.\. A promotions expects anyone able to shut the big bird's mouth."
\n<Soldier>Oi partner..\.\.\. cut me some slack,\. will ya?\.\. Having to deal with those bulls can worn you out,\. ya know?
\n<Soldier>Take this...\.\.\. and leave me alone now...
\n<Soldier>Still he'e?!\.\. I told ya t' leave me alone.
\n<Soldier>Watcha doin' here?\.\. 'am not doing anything bad here,\. now scram!
"Unauthorized personnel is banned from accessing the \ia[75].\.\. Handle with care,\. exposing unprepared subjects may be lethal."
"Exec. Emma Office".\.\. You'll need a \c[18]key\c[0] to get in there.
This scene will be ready in one of the next builds!\.\. Thank you for playing up to this point!
\n<\n[1]>This place sure was something...\.\.\. but now it's over~
\n<\n[1]>Tsk.\.\. What's with all the damn security?\.\. Those big brutes are a pain...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>These people care way too much about their precious hole.\.\. A lift shouldn't be this hard to get to...\.\.\.
Neneko approaches the Gate,\. glaring at it.\.\. It's larger and more impressive than the previous ones.\.\. Excessive,\. in her opinion.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Big door like this...\.\.\. it's gotta be the last one.\.\. Alright,\. get this thing open and get moving...\.\.\.
\n<???>Damn...\.\.\. so there really is a rat scurrying around in here...\.\.\.
Several pairs of footsteps approach.\.\. Neneko turns around,\. entering a combat stance immediately.\.\.
\n<???>Eh...?\.\. Gettin' a look at you,\. looks like it's a stray cat instead,\. huh.\.\.
A dark-skinned woman lugging a large mace over her shoulder walks towards Neneko,\. stopping a small distance away.\.\.
She's flanked by two more of those large Guards.\.\. Neneko notices that the trio have boxed her in,\. with the locked gate behind her.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Shit...\.\.\. and who are you supposed to be?\.\. The cavalry?\.\.
The girl...\.\.\. yawns.\.\. She looks like she just got out of bed.\.\.
She reaches a hand up and scratches her head,\. releasing a deep breath before peering at Neneko.\.\.
\n<???>...\.\.\.I thought I'd finally get some sleep.\.\. This place really messes up my hours.\.\. I was hoping maybe finally I'd get some shut-eye...\.\.\.
\n<???>But then I hear the Oxen Guards getting loud,\. and those creaky gates slamming open when I know they're not supposed to.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Sad story.\.\. So,\. what?\.\. You the big tough girl around here?\.\.
\n<???>Hah...\.\.\. yeah,\. could say that.\.\. Guardian of the Lift,\. or whatever.\.\. Don't really care about titles,\. it's all just work either way.\.\.
\n<???>So,\. guess I gotta do my job today.\.\.
The grip on her mace tightens.\.\. She rolls her shoulders,\. cracking her neck.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Hah!\.\. What,\. you gonna fight me in your pajamas,\. afro?!\.\.
\n<???>Does it matter?\.\. It's all the same.\.\. Besides,\. I'm wrapping this up asap and going straight back to bed.\.\.
\n<???>I won't even bother asking you to leave.\.\. You look like the type that doesn't know when to quit.\.\.

\n<???>...\.\.\. Honestly,\. I don't feel like dealing with you coming back,\. either.\.\. \BST[3]So if you don't mind,\. I'm just gonna get rid of you for good and head back to my room,\. real quick.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Damn...\.\.\. you're cranky when you're tired,\. huh?\.\. Whatever,\. girl.\.\. \BST[3]If you're the toughest of this bunch,\. you're right,\. this will be quick!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I've got business past this gate and you're wasting my time!\.\. You got problems sleeping then I'll help get the lights out before I take that lift!\.\.
She dashes forward,\. claws bared.\.\. With a threatening cry,\. the catgirl swipes at the scrawnier woman.\.\.
...\.\.\. Only to hit nothing but air,\. as the guard evaded,\. merely sidestepping and tilting her head away from Neneko's attack.\.\.
A bit of movement from the corner of her eye is all the cue Neneko needs to leap away from the woman.\.\.
Narrowly,\. she managed to avoid the swing of her heavy mace,\. only the air moved by the swing hitting her instead.\.\.
She doesn't move from her spot,\. letting her mace thunk on the ground before lifting it up and draping it on her shoulder.\.\.
But in a simple movement the Guard raises her mace to block the attack.\.\. She's barely even pushed,\. despite Neneko's size advantage.\.\.
With a flick of her mace,\. the Guardian forces Neneko to disengage,\. the catgirl being flung back several feet.\.\.
She rights herself quickly,\. entering a fighting stance.\.\.
The Guardian rubs her eyes,\. before lifting her mace,\. pointing it at Neneko.\.\.
Neneko rolls on the floor,\. grunting.\.\. In a second she's back on her feet,\. panting,\. glaring at the other woman.\.\.
\n<???>Huh...\.\.\. you're harder to put down than the usual trespassers,\. honestly.\.\. \BST[1]I guess that's my bad.\.\. I forgot you mana pumped beast types are more stubborn.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Hah...\.\.\. who're you calling a beast?\.\. If anything,\. the beast around here is you!\.\. \BST[3]How am I not hitting you?\.\.
The girl yawns,\. dragging her mace behind her as she steps forward.\.\.
\n<???>C'mon.\.\. You really asking me that?\.\. If some stray could put me down I would've been out of a job ages ago.\.\. Even if this job is a pain.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Hah...\.\.\. for someone that looks like they haven't slept in weeks you're definitely something,\. I'll give ya that...\.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>You're still going down,\. though!\.\. I'm still in this!\.\.
\n<???>Mmm...\.\.\. see,\. I knew it.\.\. Just don't know when to quit...\.\.\. I hate people like that.\.\. They're just...\.\.\. exhausting.\.\.
\n<???>You've lasted longer than I wanted you to.\.\. That's mostly on me,\. but...\.\.\. I guess I have to be a little more serious if you're not going to make this easy.\.\.
The Boss hefts her mace off of her shoulder,\. turning it and planting it on the ground,\. placing her hands atop the handle as she gazes at Neneko.\.\.
Despite herself,\. the cat tenses,\. the woman's glare suddenly...\.\.\. much more threatening.\.\.
\n<Emma>Stray Cat,\. my name is Emma,\. the mightiest of the Oxen.\.\. The Guardian of the Lift.\.\.This is my territory,\. and it is my duty to guard it from those unworthy or unwelcome.\.\.
\n<Emma>On this ground I call my home you have trespassed,\. and thus by the rules have personally challenged me.\.\.
\n<Emma>Out of respect for your tenacity I have given you my name.\.\. Will you return the favor?\.\.
\n<Emma>Alright then...\.\.\. Neneko,\. to you I'll say...\.\.\.
It happened in an instant.\.\. One moment,\. the Guardian had been standing a fair distance away,\. her mace down.\.\.
And then the next moment,\. all Neneko could see were Emma's exhausted eyes,\. glaring right at her.\.\.
She had closed the distance faster than the cat could blink,\. and--
A hard,\. heavy weight suddenly smashes into Neneko's stomach,\. with all the force of a boulder barreling at high speed,\. it felt like.\.\.
The tip of Emma's mace,\. at some point,\. had embedded itself into her gut.\.\.
Neneko could only cough out as all the air was forced out of her before she knew it.\.\.
Her limp,\. struck body sails through the air,\. and suddenly a spike of pain crawls all throughout her back.\.\.
If she were more lucid she would have noticed that she had collided with the Gate,\. and then promptly went straight through it.\.\.
Judging from the second spike of pain in her back,\. Neneko could only imagine there was another door past the Gate that she had also smashed through.\.\.
